        <a title="Rose" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Rose" href="/user/show/1953408-rose">Rose</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title=" 9780710089045" href="/book/show/1028954.The_Muqaddimah">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer65783303" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer441160996977117540">A fascinating look at the history (and geography) of the world from the perspective of a well-traveled Islamic scholar/politician in the 14th century (late golden age of Islam). It also includes, among many other things, a detailed discussion of how to tell real prophets from fake. I remember that part, I think, because it drove home for me how very different his world and mindset are from mine.</span>

          </span>
        </div>


