        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer4346240515" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1755894283133348385">Khaldun&apos;s book is a kind of emblem of the Islamic brightening periods. The kind of precision regarding so many topics is a perfect example of measuring the golden times, which produce this kind of depth intellectuals. <br/><br/>Khaldun discussed a lot of the topics in his book, from history to the rising and falling of civilizations, what are the reason behind the emergence of leaders, how they forge within their societies, why are agrarian people are not going to be equal to the sedentary people, sorcery</span>
  <span id="freeText1755894283133348385" style="display:none">Khaldun's book is a kind of emblem of the Islamic brightening periods. The kind of precision regarding so many topics is a perfect example of measuring the golden times, which produce this kind of depth intellectuals. <br /><br />Khaldun discussed a lot of the topics in his book, from history to the rising and falling of civilizations, what are the reason behind the emergence of leaders, how they forge within their societies, why are agrarian people are not going to be equal to the sedentary people, sorcery and magic effects in human's lives, what are the great aspects and pillars of the Islamic religion, what is philosophy, theology and spirituality according to his opinion. Many other topics have been exquisitely posited in his book "The Mukadamah". <br /><br />If anyone wants to understand the impacts of the gaps mostly happening to all of the situations during the raising and falling of the civilizations, what are the detailed reasons behind the rise and fall, they should have to go through his book.</span>
  <a data-text-id="1755894283133348385" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
